  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Officer (Talent Acquisition)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Manage the end-to-end recruitment cycle and provide comprehensive HR support to ensure compliance with statutory requirements and effective HR operations.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Execute full recruitment cycle from job postings to new hire onboarding, ensuring a streamlined and timely hiring process that meets organizational needs</li><li>Provide full range support in HR duties including recruitment and selection, preparation of contract, new hire orientation, employee relations, and manpower planning etc.</li><li>Manage and process employee Work Pass in accordance with statutory requirements; monitoring the work passes for company.</li><li>Manage HR Administrative duties such as preparation of all HR related letters, Work Pass (Work Permit, S/Employment Pass) applications for renewal and cancellations, insurance, maintaining Employee P-File and HR Documentation</li><li>Ensure company regulations and practices are in accordance to the Employment Act and Statutory requirements.</li><li>Knowledge of Payroll, Learning & Development is an advantage.</li><li>Any others ad-hoc duties related to work scope as assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Human Resource Management/Business Administration or related fields </li><li>At least 1 - 2 years of relevant working experience in Recruitment within built environment or related fields/industry</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office </li><li>Possess good knowledge of Employment Act and MOM employment rules</li></ul><p></p>",
